## **SECTION 2: AT-RISK PIPELINE TABLE**

### Purpose
Identify and display order lines that are **at risk of becoming delayed** based on:
1. Their current production/delivery stage (early or intermediate stages)
2. Time remaining until the due date (within 60 days)

### Qualifying Criteria for At-Risk Items
An order line appears in this table ONLY if ALL of the following conditions are TRUE:

```
Condition 1 - Stage Check:
  The current Stage must be one of:
  • "Initial Stage"
  • "Intermediate Stage"
  • "Yet to Start"
  • "Yet to launch"
  • "NO RM"
  • "Intermediate"

Condition 2 - Future Due Date:
  Days Until Due must be GREATER than 0 (not past due)

Condition 3 - Within 60-Day Window:
  Days Until Due must be LESS THAN OR EQUAL TO 60
```

**If ANY condition is false, the row should display as blank/empty**

### Table Structure

| Column | Header | Source Field | Description |
|--------|--------|--------------|-------------|
| 1 | Item # | Item # (Column D) | Part number |
| 2 | Supplier | Supplier (Column B) | Supplier name |
| 3 | Site | Site (Column C) | Delivery location |
| 4 | Due Date | Due Date (Column G) | Expected delivery date |
| 5 | Days Until Due | Days Until Due (Column P) | Days remaining |
| 6 | Stage | Stage (Column I) | Current production stage |
| 7 | Risk Level | *Calculated* | Urgency classification |

### Days until due calculation logic


This formula is used in the "Days Until Due" column of the At-Risk Pipeline table. Here's what it does step-by-step:

What This Formula Does:
"Show me the number of days until this order is due, BUT ONLY IF the order is in an early/risky production stage AND is due within the next 60 days. Otherwise, show nothing."

Breaking It Down:
Part	What It Checks	Plain English
MATCH(CW_Data!I59, {"Initial Stage","Intermediate Stage","Yet to Start","Yet to launch","NO RM","Intermediate"}, 0)	Is the Stage risky?	"Is this order's current stage one of the 'at-risk' stages?" (stages that are early in the process and might not finish on time)
ISNUMBER(...)	Did we find a match?	"Did we find the stage in our list of risky stages? If yes, this returns TRUE"
CW_Data!P59 > 0	Is it a future order?	"Is this order due in the future (not already past due)?"
CW_Data!P59 <= 60	Is it due within 60 days?	"Is this order due within the next 60 days?"
* (multiply)	All conditions must be TRUE	The multiplication acts like AND logic — ALL three conditions must be true
CW_Data!P59	The value to display	"If all conditions pass, show the actual 'Days Until Due' value"
""	Otherwise blank	"If any condition fails, show nothing (blank cell)"
IFERROR(..., "")	Error handling	"If anything goes wrong (like missing data), just show blank instead of an error"
The Three Conditions (ALL must be TRUE):
✅ Condition 1: Stage is "at-risk" (Initial, Intermediate, Yet to Start, Yet to launch, NO RM, or Intermediate)
     AND
✅ Condition 2: Days Until Due > 0 (order is not past due)
     AND  
✅ Condition 3: Days Until Due ≤ 60 (order is due within the next 60 days)
Why This Logic?
This formula filters the At-Risk Pipeline to show only orders that need attention NOW:

Orders in early stages that might not finish on time
Orders that are coming up soon (within 60 days)
Excludes past-due orders (handled separately)
Excludes orders far in the future (low urgency)
Example Outcomes:
Stage	Days Until Due	Result	Why
Initial Stage	15	15	✅ At-risk stage, future, within 60 days
Shipped	10	(blank)	❌ "Shipped" is not an at-risk stage
Intermediate Stage	-5	(blank)	❌ Past due (negative days)
Initial Stage	75	(blank)



### Risk Level Calculation Logic

**Plain English:** Assign a risk level based on how many days remain until the due date. Closer dates = higher risk.

```
IF Days Until Due ≤ 7 days:
    Display: "🚨 CRITICAL"
    Priority: Highest - Immediate attention required
    
ELSE IF Days Until Due ≤ 14 days (8-14):
    Display: "🔴 HIGH"
    Priority: High - Escalate and expedite
    
ELSE IF Days Until Due ≤ 30 days (15-30):
    Display: "🟡 MEDIUM"
    Priority: Medium - Monitor closely
    
ELSE (31-60 days):
    Display: "🔵 WATCH"
    Priority: Low - Track progress
```

### Risk Level Thresholds Summary
| Days Until Due | Icon | Risk Level | Action Required |
|----------------|------|------------|-----------------|
| 1-7 days | 🚨 | CRITICAL | Immediate escalation |
| 8-14 days | 🔴 | HIGH | Expedite and monitor daily |
| 15-30 days | 🟡 | MEDIUM | Review weekly, escalate if no progress |
| 31-60 days | 🔵 | WATCH | Track in regular reviews |

